    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 1 vs. required Gradation 2) is accepted on the basis that the ASTM F1717 protocol is standardized and the single-condition limitation is conservative relative to clinical loading. Overall model risk level 3 with Medium assurance level is deemed sufficient for the intended regulatory decision. The revised output-comparison dataset (incorporated post-signing) does not alter the acceptance conclusion; however, the package should be re-signed to restore consistency.",
